# Plan: `.sentryclirc` Config File Support

## Goal
Add backward-compatible support for `.sentryclirc` INI config files, solving:
- Per-directory org/project defaults for monorepos
- Global defaults via `~/.sentryclirc`
- Backward compat with old sentry-cli config files

**No new commands.** `.sentryclirc` files are the config mechanism. The existing (empty) SQLite defaults table remains as a lower-priority fallback.

## Resolution Chain (after changes)

```
1. Explicit CLI args          (highest)
2. Environment variables      (SENTRY_ORG, SENTRY_PROJECT, SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN, etc.)
3. .sentryclirc file          ← NEW (walked up from CWD, merged with global)
4. SQLite defaults            (unchanged, still unpopulated)
5. DSN auto-detection
6. Directory name inference   (lowest)
```

`.sentryclirc` values for `token` and `url` are applied via env shim (set the corresponding `process.env` vars if not already set). Org/project are inserted directly into the resolution chain for proper source tracking.

## Design

### `.sentryclirc` format (INI, matching old sentry-cli)
```ini
[defaults]
org = my-org
project = my-project
url = https://sentry.io/

[auth]
token = sntrys_...
```

### Walk-up behavior
1. Start at `cwd`, walk toward filesystem root
2. At each directory, check for `.sentryclirc`
3. Collect all found files (closest-first order)
4. Always also check global: `$SENTRY_CONFIG_DIR/.sentryclirc`, then `~/.sentryclirc`
5. Merge: per-field, closest file wins; global fills gaps

### Env shim (token + url)
Applied early in `startCli()` before any command dispatch:
- `[auth] token` → `process.env.SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN` (if env var unset)
- `[defaults] url` → `process.env.SENTRY_URL` (if `SENTRY_HOST` and `SENTRY_URL` both unset)

This avoids changes to `auth.ts` and `constants.ts`. The existing env var handling picks up the values naturally.

### Resolution chain insertion (org + project)
Inserted as paired check (both org AND project required, matching existing pattern) in:
- `resolveOrgAndProject()` — between env vars (line ~983) and SQLite defaults (line ~986)
- `resolveAllTargets()` — between env vars (line ~812) and SQLite defaults (line ~816)
- `resolveOrg()` — between env vars (line ~1051) and SQLite defaults (line ~1055), org-only
- `resolveOrgsForListing()` — between env vars (line ~1191) and SQLite defaults (line ~1193), org-only

Source tracking: `detectedFrom: ".sentryclirc (<filepath>)"`

