## Implementation Details

### 1. INI Parser (`src/lib/ini.ts`)

```typescript
export type IniData = Record<string, Record<string, string>>;
export function parseIni(content: string): IniData;
```

Rules:
- `[section]` headers → section name lowercased, trimmed
- `key = value` → key lowercased, value trimmed
- `#` and `;` line comments (not inline — tokens can contain `#`)
- Keys before any section → `""` (empty) section
- Quoted values: strip matching outer `"` or `'` quotes
- Strip UTF-8 BOM
- Duplicate keys: last wins. Duplicate sections: merged
- Malformed lines: silently skip (debug log)
- No multi-line values

### 2. `.sentryclirc` Reader (`src/lib/sentryclirc.ts`)

```typescript
export type SentryCliRcConfig = {
  org?: string;
  project?: string;
  url?: string;
  token?: string;
  sources: { org?: string; project?: string; url?: string; token?: string };
};

/** Load and cache .sentryclirc (process-lifetime cache keyed by cwd) */
export function loadSentryCliRc(cwd: string): SentryCliRcConfig;

/** Apply env shim for token/url. Call once early in boot. */
export function applySentryCliRcEnvShim(cwd: string): void;
```

Walk-up uses `existsSync` + `readFileSync` (synchronous — the walk reads at most ~20 tiny files, matches `getDefaultOrganization()` sync pattern). Cycle detection via `realpathSync` + `Set<string>`. File read errors silently ignored (ENOENT, EACCES).

### 3. `cli.ts` boot integration

```typescript
// In startCli(), before args parsing
export function startCli(): Promise<void> {
  applySentryCliRcEnvShim(process.cwd());
  const args = process.argv.slice(2);
  // ... existing code
}
```

### 4. Resolution chain insertion (in `resolve-target.ts`)

Pattern for each function (example for `resolveOrgAndProject`):

```typescript
// After env var check, before SQLite defaults:
const rcConfig = loadSentryCliRc(cwd);
if (rcConfig.org && rcConfig.project) {
  return withTelemetryContext({
    org: rcConfig.org,
    project: rcConfig.project,
    orgDisplay: rcConfig.org,
    projectDisplay: rcConfig.project,
    detectedFrom: `.sentryclirc (${rcConfig.sources.project})`,
  });
}
```

For org-only functions (`resolveOrg`, `resolveOrgsForListing`), check only `rcConfig.org`.

## Test Plan

### Property-based tests (fast-check)

**`ini.property.test.ts`:**
- Round-trip: `parseIni(serialize(data)) ≡ data` for generated IniData
- Idempotency: `parseIni(serialize(parseIni(x))) ≡ parseIni(x)`
- Comment immunity: inserting `# ...` lines doesn't change result
- Key/section case insensitivity
- Last-write-wins for duplicate keys

**`sentryclirc.property.test.ts`:**
- Merge monotonicity: adding a config file never removes resolved fields
- Closest-wins: closest file always takes priority per-field

### Unit tests

**`ini.test.ts`:**
- Empty file, comments-only file, BOM handling
- Quoted value stripping (matched/mismatched quotes)
- Real-world `.sentryclirc` from old CLI docs
- Malformed lines (no `=`, unclosed section, empty key)

**`sentryclirc.test.ts`:**
- No files found → empty config
- Single local `.sentryclirc` → populated config
- Global fills gaps when local is partial
- Closest file wins for overlapping keys
- Env shim: sets `SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN` only if unset
- Env shim: sets `SENTRY_URL` only if `SENTRY_HOST` and `SENTRY_URL` both unset
- Process-lifetime cache returns same reference on second call
- `SENTRY_CONFIG_DIR` override for global path lookup

### Existing test updates
- `test/lib/resolve-target.test.ts` — mock `loadSentryCliRc`, verify it slots between env vars and SQLite defaults

## Edge Cases

| Scenario | Behavior |
|----------|----------|
| Invalid INI syntax | Malformed lines skipped; valid lines still parsed |
| Token in `.sentryclirc` expired/revoked | API returns 401; normal auth error flow applies |
| `.sentryclirc` org conflicts with DSN org | `.sentryclirc` wins (higher priority, DSN never consulted) |
| Only `org` in `.sentryclirc`, no `project` | Org used for org-only resolution; `resolveOrgAndProject` falls through to next step |
| Symlinks in walk-up | `realpathSync` resolves them; cycle detected via `Set` |
| File permission denied | Silently skipped; other files still contribute |
| Library mode (SDK invoke) | `applySentryCliRcEnvShim` only called from CLI entry; library mode uses `setEnv()` separately |

